### === TEST SANTÉ SERVICES ===

### 1. Python RAG Service Health
GET http://localhost:8000/health
Accept: application/json

### === TEST ENDPOINTS RAG ===

### 2. Lister tous les patterns (20+)
GET http://localhost:8000/rag/patterns
Accept: application/json

### 3. Voir les stats KB
GET http://localhost:8000/rag/stats
Accept: application/json

### 4. Récupérer un pattern spécifique
GET http://localhost:8000/rag/patterns/py_001
Accept: application/json

### === TEST RETRIEVAL (Core RAG) ===

### 5. Récupérer patterns similaires (Python code)
POST http://localhost:8000/rag/retrieve
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "def hello():\n    print('test')",
  "language": "python",
  "category": "style"
}

### === TEST CRUD OPERATIONS ===

### 6. Créer un nouveau pattern
POST http://localhost:8000/rag/patterns
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "custom_001",
  "name": "My Custom Pattern",
  "language": "python",
  "category": "bug",
  "description": "Avoid mutable default arguments",
  "rule": "Never use mutable objects as default arguments",
  "example": "def foo(lst=[]):",
  "fix": "def foo(lst=None):"
}

### 7. Mettre à jour un pattern
PUT http://localhost:8000/rag/patterns/custom_001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Custom Pattern",
  "rule": "Updated rule description"
}

### 8. Supprimer un pattern
DELETE http://localhost:8000/rag/patterns/custom_001
Accept: application/json

### === TEST BACKEND API ===

### 9. Test Health Backend
GET http://localhost:3001/api/health
Accept: application/json

### 10. Analyzer avec RAG (Full Pipeline)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "def foo(arr=[]):\n    arr.append(1)\n    return arr",
  "language": "python",
  "category": "bugs"
}
